Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
To cross a street, you have to very careful and should not be involved in any kind of distracting activity. Look both sides for any oncoming traffic. If you judge that even by the slightest chance you wont be able to safely make it to the other side, wait. Else, swiftly cross the street and take comfort in the fact you have learnt how to cross a street from me, well.